Class Camp

Object
Camp
public class Camp extends Object
The Camp class represents a camp with participants comprising of attendees and committee members. It holds camp-specific enquiries, suggestions, and other relevant camp details. It allows the managing of camp details, attendees, and committee members, and the handling of enquiries and suggestions.

Example usage: 

 Camp myCamp = new Camp("Summer Camp", 20230101, 20231231, 20221201, "Camp Location", 100, 5, "Description", "Staff Name", true, "Faculty");
 myCamp.addAttendee(new Student("John Doe", "123456789"));
 myCamp.viewCampInfo();
Author:
Zixin, Tey Cia Meng

  • Constructor Details

    • Camp

      public Camp(String campName, int startDate, int endDate, int registrationClosingDate, boolean open, String location, int participantSlots, int campCommitteeSlots, String campDescription, String name, boolean visibility, String faculty)
      Constructs a new Camp with specified details.
      Parameters:
      campName - Name of the camp.
      startDate - Start date of the camp.
      endDate - End date of the camp.
      registrationClosingDate - Closing date for camp registration, after which no signups are valid.
      open - Open to whole NTU or specific faculty only
      location - Location of the camp.
      participantSlots - Total number of attendee slots, inclusive of committee slots.
      campCommitteeSlots - Number of committee slots (max 10).
      campDescription - A description of the camp.
      name - Name of the staff-in-charge of the camp created.
      visibility - Visibility status of the camp to whole NTU, with false being visible only to faculty.
      faculty - Faculty associated with the camp.

      public String getDateInString(int date)
      Converts an integer representation of a date into a formatted string.

      The input integer should be in the format "yyyyMMdd," and the output string will be formatted as "yyyy-MM-dd."

      Parameters:
      date - The integer representation of the date in "yyyyMMdd" format.
      Returns:
      A formatted string representation of the date in "yyyy-MM-dd" format.
      Throws:
      DateTimeParseException - If the input date cannot be parsed successfully.
